<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id123f93ac-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s2308"><num value="2308">§ 2308.</num><heading> Tax exemption for gifts</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Gifts and bequests received by the Board under this chapter, and the income from them are exempt from taxes.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id123f93ad-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1293">82 Stat. 1293</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id123f93ae-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id123f93af-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 300gg (<ref href="/us/act/1941-07-09/ch284/s7">July 9, 1941, ch. 284, § 7</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/55/582">55 Stat. 582</ref>).</p>
</note>
</notes>
